news.title: Ghaziabad: Wave City developers claims protests prevent allottees from building houses
news.para: Wave City, a part of the Hi-Tech integrated township policy, ran into rough weather for various reasons since 2021. On Aug 5 this year, the GDA board approved a revised detailed project report of the township. This raised the hope of about 12,000 allottees who invested in the project.

news.title: WeWork leases 1.43 lakh sq ft office space to IBM, OpenText in Bengaluru
news.para: WeWork has leased 1.43 lakh square feet of office space to IBM and OpenText at Embassy Golf Links Business Park in Bengaluru. IBM and OpenText have each taken around 70,000 sq ft for two years. This reflects the growing demand for managed office spaces, especially in the IT sector.

news.title: Chandigarh administration issues notices to 4,000 homes for rooftop solar installations
news.para: The notices, sent to owners of homes of 500 sq yard and above by UT estate department recently, have asked for installation of plants within two months under the Chandigarh Building Rules (Urban).

news.title: Godrej Properties board meeting on October 1 to consider fundraising through securities
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Godrej Properties informed that a meeting of the board of directors is scheduled to be held on October 1 to discuss and consider the proposal to raise funds by way of the issue of equity shares, or any other eligible securities and/or instruments.

news.title: Kochi Metro Rail proposes new metro line from Kazhakkoottam to Putharikandam
news.para: The earlier plan to begin the service at Technocity in Pallippuram was abandoned after govt issued a directive to consider a new alignment. This decision was made after realizing that National Highways Authority of India (NHAI) may not give its nod to dig up roads for the construction of Metro pillars, citing the ‘defect liability' period.

news.title: Delhi: DDA extends final payment deadline for Dwarka flats to October 31
news.para: The authority stated that the decision was taken after considering buyers' requests for more time to manage their finances and the ongoing finishing work in the flats.

news.title: US new home sales drop in August 2024
news.para: New single-family home sales came in at an annual rate of 716,000, seasonally adjusted, lower than July's revised 751,000 figure, said the Commerce Department.

news.title: Haveri civic body’s commercial complexes vacant for six years due to high rent
news.para: ​​Despite multiple attempts to auction these spaces, local vendors have shown little interest in procuring them, leading to the waste of crores of public funds and the deterioration of these complexes.

news.title: Illegal constructions continue on Raipur lake despite RMC intervention
news.para: One such lake, Sheetla Talab, which is a significant water body situated in the residential area of Avanti Vihar Sector-2 of Raipur, is facing threats from illegal constructions on its banks. These encroachments not only affect the lake's ecological balance but also its cultural importance.

news.title: Karnataka HC issues notice to state government, BBMP over illegal EWS land mortgage
news.para: Justice Hemant Chandanagoudar also ordered notice to Maverick Holdings and Investments Pvt Ltd, Garuda Maverick Infrastructure Project Pvt Ltd, Embassy Garuda Reality Ventures LLP, Sammaan Capital Ltd, and Lokayukta police, while adjourning the hearing to Sept 30.

news.title: IndoSpace leases 30,000 sq ft warehouse to Robinsons Global Logistics in Gujarat
news.para: This lease for a term of five years is part of Robinsons Global Logistics Solutions’ expansion plan and adds to its footprint of over one million sq ft of warehousing space across India.

news.title: HYDRAA launches survey to address government land encroachments in Ameenpur
news.para: ​​This action follows numerous complaints on encroachment of park land in layouts approved by the Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA), particularly in survey numbers 152 and 153 of Venkataramana Colony.

news.title: Goa: Sancoale panchayat to issue notice to Bhutani Infra's project
news.para: The meeting which lasted for three hours decided to issue the show cause notice that will be returnable within seven days, asking Parmesh Construction why the licence should not be revoked for various violations.

news.title: NGT criticizes SEIAA for delaying environmental clearance for Gurugram colony
news.para: A resident of Malibu Towne had in 2022 filed a petition with NGT alleging that 10 diesel generators were operating illegally in a green belt in the colony, and construction and demolition (C&D) waste dumping was rampant in the area.

news.title: Mumbai architects urge BMC to protect open spaces from infrastructure projects
news.para: We urge you to build on the solidarity we witnessed at Patwardhan Park and make a lasting commitment: that all open spaces in Mumbai remain open and accessible to the public in perpetuity, under public control. Safeguarding these spaces is vital for the city's environmental, social, and economic future," states the letter.

news.title: YEIDA reports Rs 982.51 crore revenue in H1 FY25
news.para: A large portion of this expenditure, around Rs 799 crore, was directed toward land acquisition — more than double the Rs 362 crore spent on the same last year. According to officials, the Authority is focused on creating a substantial land bank to support future developments along the expressway corridor.

news.title: NBR Group acquires 9.65 acres land in Bengaluru for residential project
news.para: NBR Group has acquired a 9.65-acre land parcel in Bengaluru's Sarjapur-Mullur suburb to develop a high-rise residential project. This project, estimated to generate over Rs 1200 crore, will cater to the growing demand for premium housing in the area, driven by its strategic location and infrastructure developments.

news.title: Bengaluru: Puravankara acquires 2.3 acres land from Citrus Venture Projects for Rs 135 crore
news.para: The property, located in Hebbal, has a development potential of 2 million square feet in the first phase of the acquisition. Additionally, the firm is in the process of procuring around 10 acres of land from Citrus Venture Projects in Hebbal.

news.title: HomeLane acquires DesignCafe, raises Rs 225 crore
news.para: After the acquisition, HomeLane raised Rs 225 crore from new investors, including Sunil Kant Munjal’s Hero Enterprise and Claypond Capital, the family office of Manipal Group’s Ranjan Pai, with participation from existing investors such as WestBridge Capital and others.

news.title: OECD calls for higher property taxes to fight debt
news.para: In its economic oulook report titled "Turning the Corner", the Paris-based organisation said global gross domestic product would expand by 3.2 percent, compared to 3.1 percent in its previous forecast.
